# No Co-authored-by: Cursor

NEVER include `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>` or any variation of `Co-authored-by: Cursor` in commit messages, PR descriptions, code comments, or any file content.

## Rules

- Strip `Co-authored-by` trailers from all commit messages before committing
- Never add `Co-authored-by` lines when creating commits
- If a git hook or automation injects it, amend the commit to remove it
- Do not include Cursor attribution in PR bodies or descriptions
- Do not leave any trace of Cursor co-authorship anywhere in the repository

## When committing

Always use `--no-gpg-sign` is NOT required, but you MUST ensure the commit message body does NOT contain any line matching:

```
Co-authored-by: Cursor*
```

If you see it in `git log -1`, immediately amend to remove it.
